        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 30 at 1:32PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 132 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 13 miles northeast of Clarksville to
over Purley, or extending from 13 miles northeast of Clarksville to
10 miles northwest of Leesburg, moving east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mount Pleasant, New Boston, Pittsburg, Boxelder, Hooks, Mount
Vernon, Daingerfield, Hughes Springs, De Kalb, Lone Star, Naples,
Redwater, Maud, Omaha, Us 259 And I 30 Intersection, Dalby
Springs, Rocky Branch, Cookville, Wilkerson and Cason.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
